The paper deals with a linear minimum mean square error (LMMSE) filter for random processes, which is a topic related to information theory (cs.IT) and signal processing (cs.SP). The proposed method is based on a graph representation, which is a common technique in machine learning (cs.LG) and multimedia (cs.MM). The paper also discusses the use of a priori information, which is a topic related to statistical inference (cs.SI).
